{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"frying pan, refrigerator, hob","id":"r102072","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-yzQKOWRkrf4\/XZQv4z76JwI\/AAAAAAAAcgw\/unjQFTxAnHQQEQa4ZVd5IwwQz7yVOMIewCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_PKmkj6JGY84FAeJm.png","title":"Beef Burger with Melting Cheese Centre","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"2 slices sliced white bread (approx. 95 g)"},{"content":"water, for soaking"},{"content":"5 g fresh parsley leaves"},{"content":"130 g red onions, quartered"},{"content":"20 g sunflower oil, plus 1 tsp for frying"},{"content":"1 medium egg"},{"content":"½ Tbsp English mustard, or to taste"},{"content":"1 tsp hot paprika"},{"content":"1 tsp fine sea salt"},{"content":"½ tsp ground pepper"},{"content":"500 g beef mince, broken in pieces"},{"content":"120 g Cheddar cheese, in 6 pieces (4 cm x 4 cm x 1 cm)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"23.4 g","fat":"30.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"9.2 g","calories":"1703 kJ \/ 407 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Soak bread in water then squeeze dry and set aside."},{"content":"Place parsley in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Add onions and oil then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved soaked and drained bread, egg, mustard, paprika, salt, pepper and beef mince then mix <b>30 sec\/\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Divide mixture into 6 balls,  place a piece of Cheddar in centre and enclose burger mince around cheese so cheese is not visible. Flatten to form burgers (Ø 9 cm) and transfer to a plate, then refrigerate for 20 minutes."},{"content":"Heat oil in a large frying pan. Cook burgers over a medium heat for 4-5 minutes on each side until cooked through. Allow burgers  to stand in frying pan, off the heat, for 2-3 minutes to allow cheese to firm up a little. Serve in a bun of your choice."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serving suggestion: grill burger buns in the oven or toaster, so they are crispy. Serve with ketchup or avocado mayonnaise, lettuce, coleslaw or pickles.","Feta also works well instead of Cheddar."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","45m","6 portions"]}